news.title: Mahindra Lifespaces acquires 8.2 acre land in Bengaluru
news.para: Mahindra Lifespace Developers' land has a developable potential of approximately 0.9 million sq ft of saleable area and a projected gross development value (GDV) of almost Rs 1,000 crore.

news.title: Housing allotted to tribals in PVTG villages to be completed by March 2026: ASR collector
news.para: Through a power point presentation, the collector elaborated about the implementation of the scheme in the district, explaining the challenges faced in construction and the steps being taken to overcome them.

news.title: Haryana govt proposes policy allowing tree felling on urban land allotted for projects
news.para: The policy is proposed to supersede all previous orders related to tree felling outside of forests, even if those areas are notified under Section 3 of the Punjab Land Preservation Act (PLPA), 1900

news.title: Kolkata civic body stops work of under construction high-rise building
news.para: In the latest incident, the Kolkata Municipal Corporation (KMC) halted construction of the five-storey building on Christopher Road in Tangra after it was found leaning dangerously towards an adjacent high-rise.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh cabinet give approval for municipal bonds in Prayagraj, Varanasi, Agra
news.para: "Through these municipal bonds, the funds will be raised from the market, with a grant of Rs 13 crore provided for every Rs 100 crore raised. The government of India will deposit the incentive amount into an escrow account," an official statement said.

news.title: Mohali MC chief orders inquiry to hold officials accountable for illegal constructions
news.para: Days after Sohana building collapse, the Mohali municipal corporation has put the role of their former MC officials, as well as the present officials, under scrutiny for neglect in checking and stopping illegal construction of buildings under MC limits.

news.title: Jharkhand housing board to allot 181 flats through lottery system from February
news.para: The allotment will be for a 90-year lease basis. JSHB would conduct the entire allotment process online for the first time. JSHB last alloted its properties in 2019.

news.title: Nuvama and Cushman & Wakefield's joint venture raises Rs 1,700 crore
news.para: Nuvama and Cushman & Wakefield Management's fund aims to offer investment opportunities to investors in the Indian commercial real estate sector and will focus on Grade A office spaces in top six citie

news.title: Bombay HC finds flat owners of building on Pedder Road guilty of contempt
news.para: It also directed the BMC chief to ascertain which officers were responsible for not complying with the civic body's notices as well as HC's orders and to spell out the actions against them.

news.title: Max Estates, M3M group among top bidder in Noida authority's commercial land auction
news.para: According to Noida authority, Max estates has emerged as the highest bidder for the biggest plot of 41,835 sq metre plot for over Rs 700 crore which has 40% residential area as well.

news.title: MREAT sets aside Maharashtra RERA order denying homebuyers relief
news.para: The complainants paid advance amounts in 2012, but the first promoter, Man Global, failed to provide allotment letters or execute agreements for sale. The project was later transferred to Man Realty Ltd and subsequently taken over by Purva Oak under SARFAESI provisions.

news.title: Bhopal: EOW launches probe into alleged irregularities in Sahara Group's land sale
news.para: The PE has been registered against officials of Sahara Housing Corporation Investment Group, various companies authorised by the Sahara Group for land sale, the concerned revenue officers and others.

news.title: Sovereign wealth fund buys 25% stake in London's Mayfair district
news.para: The 2.3 million square feet portfolio is predominately office and retail assets clustered around Grosvenor Street and Mount Street, the fund said in a statement.

news.title: NDR InvIT acquires industrial and warehousing portfolio for Rs 706.1 crore
news.para: The deal is expected to deliver robust returns and includes properties with 100 per cent occupancy, marquee tenants, and a weighted average lease expiry (WALE) of 15.4 years, NDR InvIT said.

news.title: Pune civic body demands 15 government land parcels for key projects
news.para: Govt land falls under the jurisdiction of the district collector and PMC needs to submit a proposal of the development work to the office.

news.title: Bhubaneswar: Owners of BDA's town planning schemes worry over land conversion delays
news.para: The matter was discussed during a meeting between BDA officials and landowners, covering TP scheme no. 8, which includes Dasapur and Andharua mouzas on the outskirts here.

news.title: Mohali development body demolishes illegal structures in Nayagaon
news.para: The demolition drive was organised in two illegal colonies at Karoran village, Majri tehsil, near Nayagaon. Around 30 to 40 structures were razed during the operation.

news.title: Sunac China lands first onshore debt reduction in troubled property sector
news.para: The landmark deal enables Sunac, once one of China's largest real estate developers, to deleverage its 15.4 billion yuan ($2.11 billion) outstanding onshore debt by more than half.

news.title: Home prices in New Zealand dip as buyers wait for lower rates
news.para: Seasonally adjusted median house prices fell 1.0% in December versus the previous month, and 1.8% from the previous year.

news.title: Nuvoco Vistas Corporation posts net loss of Rs 61.37 crore in Q3 FY25
news.para: Nuvoco Vistas Corporation's net consolidated total income stood at Rs 2,409.52 crore in Q3 FY25, a minor dip of from Rs 2,431.87 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.
